snippet: The FAA has certified Boeing Co's 787-9 Dreamliner for use with General Electric Co engines, clearing the way for first deliveries of the new aircraft with the U.S.-made engines expected later this month....

headline.print_headline: FAA Certifies Boeing 787-9 With GE Engines: Document
headline.main: FAA Certifies Boeing 787-9 With GE Engines: Document

lead_paragraph: The FAA has certified Boeing Co's 787-9 Dreamliner for use with General Electric Co engines, clearing the way for first deliveries of the new aircraft with the U.S.-made engines expected later this month.
